                            <comment id="15525386" author="anoop.hbase" created="Tue, 27 Sep 2016 07:43:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So we avoid 2 objects creation (The Checksum object per type and DataCheckSum object).  But we do have a ThreadLocal read.  The ThreadLocal comes with overhead.  So am not sure abt the gain of 2 object not getting created is worth enough. I feel it is ok to create object as per demand only than going with TL.  Ya the allocation u wil see some gain.. But on net perf I dont think so.  The GC should be able to clean these objects fast.  Pls check&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15525971" author="aoxiang" created="Tue, 27 Sep 2016 12:30:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Do with a minor test, it is hard too say which is the best, so close this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
